The paper discusses a score-based algorithm for causal discovery, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is based on Bayesian networks, which are a type of graphical model commonly used in data mining (cs.DM) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the identification of Y substructures, which is a concept related to graph theory and network analysis (cs.IT).
